    <text id="B1192T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Judging by this inquiry, Jordan seems to have disappeared for a period of time
                    following his transfer out of Augusta County.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <abbr expan="Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">Bur. R. F.
                        &amp; A.L.</abbr>
                    <lb/>
                    <abbr expan="Headquarters">Hd.Qrs.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">A.C.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient">Lacey, R. S.<lb/><abbr expan="Sub Assistant Commissioner"
                            >S.A.C.</abbr> 7th <abbr expan="Sub-District">Sub.Dist.</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-10-05"><abbr expan="October">Oct.</abbr> 5, 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Richmond, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir,</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>The <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst. Comr.</abbr> desires to be
                    informed, with the least possible delay, if <hi rend="underline">J.W. Jordan</hi>
                    <abbr expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner">A.S.A.C.</abbr> has taken
                    charge of his <abbr expan="Division">Div.</abbr> and established his Head
                    Quarters at Lexington. If he has not, it is directed that you order him to
                    proceed to that place at once, or show by "Surgeons Certificate" that he is
                    unable to travel, and for how long a period, he is likely to remain so.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very <abbr expan="respectfully">respty</abbr><lb/>Your <abbr
                            expan="obedient Servant">obt. Servt.</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>Will A. Coulter<lb/><abbr expan="Brevet Captain">Bvt. Capt.</abbr> U.S.
                            Army<lb/><abbr expan="Acting Assistant Adjutant General"
                        >A.A.A.Genl.</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
